    noExtraBiblicalRecordNote: "No contemporary extra-biblical source records James's death or ministry beyond the brief account in Acts 12:2. A later medieval Spanish tradition holds that his remains were transported to Santiago de Compostela, which became a major pilgrimage site, but this legend developed many centuries after his death and has no historical basis in the 1st century.",
